{"article_id":"ziGa10NEINZcbErH","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Donald Trump speaks to reporters at the White House , September 9 , 2019 .","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"( Erin Scott/Reuters )","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"The president may have just given his Democratic rival a political lifeline at a critical moment in the 2020 campaign .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"Opinions vary widely on how to characterize Trump ' s now-infamous conversation with Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelensky .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"The president believes","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"it was \" perfect \" and \" beautiful. \"","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"In the middle are those","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"who think","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"it was bad and improper or perhaps impeachable","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"but not necessarily worth the bother this close to a national election .","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"And then there are those","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"who believe","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"we know all","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"we need to know","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"to warrant impeachment and removal right now .","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"But one thing","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"virtually every sentient being agrees on ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"even if some won ' t say so publicly ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"is that","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"if Biden weren ' t running for president","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"- and outpolling Trump in general-election matchups -","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"Trump would be a lot less interested in Biden ' s alleged misdeeds .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"And that raises the amusing possibility","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"that Trump ' s effort","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"to damage Biden","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"might , just might , end up being a blessing in disguise for the former vice president .","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"The Trump-impeachment firestorm ignited","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"just as Biden was declining a bit in the polls","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"and Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts was starting to surge .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"On September 21 , Warren pulled ( slightly )","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"in front of Biden for the first time in the Des Moines Register/CNN/Mediacom poll of Iowa Democrats .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"A few days later , a Monmouth University poll put Warren two points ahead of Biden in New Hampshire .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Democratic activists were giddy","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"that Biden ' s \" electability \" argument appeared to be imploding .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"There was also a lot of glee in Trump World about the Warren surge .","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"The Trumpists are convinced","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"Warren is much more beatable than Biden","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"because she would allow the president to run against socialism , \" Pocahontas , \" and confiscatory taxes .","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"They might be right .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"It ' s certainly true that Warren galvanizes Republicans","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"- particularly wealthy GOP donors -","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"far more","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"than Biden does .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"But more beatable than Biden is not synonymous with easily beaten .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Warren is a better campaigner than Biden","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"and leads Trump in the RealClearPolitics average of polls by four points .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"The Ukraine story is still unfolding ,","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"and there ' s too much churn and uncertainty","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"to gauge or predict its effects .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Moreover , the speculation","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"that Biden simply isn ' t up to the challenge the way","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"he once was","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"is hardly baseless .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"That said ,","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"the all-out assault on Biden just might go down in history as one of the great examples of unintended consequences in American politics .","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"One of the defining dynamics of politics today is negative partisanship .","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"As Emory University ' s Alan Abramowitz and Steven Webster wrote in 2017 ,","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"\" negative partisanship explains nearly everything in American politics today. \"","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"The idea is simple :","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"Republicans vote less for Republicans","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"than they do against Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"and vice versa .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"Hillary Clinton lost","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"because more people in several key states voted against her","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"than voted against Trump .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"The dynamic doesn ' t just explain presidential elections .","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"Democrats","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"( and various media personalities )","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"outdo each other","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"trying to goad Trump into attacking them ,","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"because they know","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"that being attacked by Trump is a boon for donations , media attention , and ratings .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"Meanwhile , Trump ' s base remains loyal","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"in part because he is so good at identifying and attacking enemies .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"In the last week , all of the Democratic candidates have rallied to Biden ' s defense .","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"Senator Kamala Harris of California ,","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"who briefly surged in the polls","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"because of her attacks on Biden ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"now says ,","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"\" Leave Joe Biden alone. \"","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"It would be nice to think","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"they ' re all motivated by a sense of honor and decency in response to what they believe to be unfair attacks .","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"But logic dictates","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"it ' s more about negative partisanship .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"The enemy of my enemy is my friend ,","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"as the proverb goes .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"Of course , things could get to the point","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"where Democrats decide to toss Biden under the train the way","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"they did Senator Al Franken of Minnesota ,","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"but","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"if Biden doesn ' t crack under the pressure","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"( a real possibility ) ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"it ' s hard to see how that happens","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"as long as impeachment remains the defining issue of our politics .","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"In 2016 , Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont caved to the pressures of negative partisanship","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"and refused to make an issue of Hillary Clinton ' s \" emails. \"","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"Warren may well feel similar pressure .","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"Hence the possibility","depth":6},{"id":98,"text":"that an attempt","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"to destroy Biden","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"could one day be remembered as his lifeline .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":201,"left":126,"right":200,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":102,"right":125,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":102,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":114,"right":124,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":114,"left":2,"right":113,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":113,"left":3,"right":112,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"par